comments.comment:
Decrease in production; 
Sample variability, batch process.  Less hours old exhaust system was used instead of the Valveless Regenerative Thermal Oxidizers.  More days with precipitation. New data was added to the TPM calcs from air quality modelling (including emissions from truck receiving, grain bin, headhouse, and hammermill).

FYI: as PM10 and PM2.5 cannot be tested due to stack conditions, the RTO TPM emission rate is conservatively assumed to equal the emission rate for PM10 and PM2.5
